				<tr>
					<td>
					
					<!-- LARGE STORY IMAGE -->
					<center><a href="http://scifi.sparklist.com/t/7996/127160/1557/0/"><img src="http://www.scifi.com/newsletters/dvice/images/080904/featured.jpg" border="0" alt="Samsung X360" style="float: right; padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 20px; padding-bottom: 10px;" /></a></center>
					
					<!-- BEGIN STORY -->
					<div clas="MainStory" style="padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px; color: #333333; font-size: 12px; line-height: 18px; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; text-decoration: none;">

					If you've fallen in love with the <a href="http://scifi.sparklist.com/t/7996/127160/389/0/" style="color: #9933CC; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; text-decoration: none;">MacBook Air</a> but just can't stand the thought of muddling through OS X, becoming a snooty Mac user, or suffering through Apple's skin-deep quality and often-shoddy workmanship, Samsung is aiming its 0.66-inch-thin X360 laptop directly at you.
					
					<br /><br />
					
					This 13.3-inch laptop weighs a mere 2.8 pounds and shines where the MacBook Air skimps: It's the inputs, stupid. How does three USB ports (compared to the Air's one), a 7-in-1 card reader (compared to the Air's none), HDMI and Ethernet ports (no such thing on the Air) and a VGA port sound? On top of that, you get Wi-Fi (of course), a 1.3-megapixel camera, an LED-backlit display, and a 128GB solid-state hard drive.
					
					<br /><br />
					
					Best yet, a couple of our buddies have laid their hands on this beauty and tell us it's as solid as a rock. Now if Samsung can just beat that MacBook Air price ($1,799) &#8212; which should be easy to do &#8212; it'll make the <a href="http://scifi.sparklist.com/t/7996/127160/423/0/" style="color: #9933CC; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; text-decoration: none;">MacBook Air look like it's for AirHeads</a>. Peek at the gallery below to see all the luxo finishes, colors and beauty of this fine machine. We want.

					<br /><br />

					
					<a href="http://scifi.sparklist.com/t/7996/127160/1558/0/" style="color: #9933CC; font-family: Arial, Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; text-decoration: none;"><b>SAMSUNG X360 GALLERY</b></a>

					</div>
